<p>That is the new book by Dan Senor and Saul Singer.  The authors argue that Israel has higher solidarity and also higher social capital than recent media reports might indicate.  They are thus optimistic about the country, and the subtitle is <em>The Surprising Resilience of a Divided Natoin in a Turbulent World</em>.</p>
<p>I do not go to Israel enough to have a strong opinion on this, but their thesis is consistent with my casual observation, and also with my intuition about negative bias in media.  The book <a href="https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Genius-Israel-Small-Nation-Teach-ebook/dp/B08VJM121D/ref=sr_1_2?crid=14R5V3F1545ND&amp;keywords=dan+senor+singer&amp;qid=1696461857&amp;sprefix=dan+senor+singer%2Caps%2C64&amp;sr=8-2" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">comes out November 7</a>.</p>
